<% content_for :title do %>Help Center | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>Publish a public Help Center knowledge base for your customers in <%= installation_brand_name %>.<% end %>

<h1>Help Center</h1>
<p class="lead">
  The <strong>Help Center</strong> is a public knowledge base <em>your business</em> publishes for <em>your customers</em>
  (e.g. FAQs, how-to articles). It is separate from this <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide on the homepage.
</p>

<h2>Public URL</h2>
<p>After creating a portal, customers access articles at:</p>
<p><code>https://your-domain.com/hc/your-portal-slug/en</code></p>
<p>No login required for readers. You control slug, locale, and branding.</p>

<h2>Create a portal</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Help Center</strong> in sidebar → create portal</li>
  <li>Name and <strong>slug</strong> (URL segment)</li>
  <li>Choose layout: <strong>Classic</strong> (help site) or <strong>Documentation</strong> (docs-style sidebar)</li>
  <li>Configure logo, colors, custom domain (optional)</li>
</ol>

<h2>Articles & categories</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Articles</strong> — write content in the built-in editor; set status to Published</li>
  <li><strong>Categories</strong> — organize articles; appear in portal navigation</li>
  <li><strong>Locales</strong> — add languages; community translations may apply on cloud</li>
</ul>

<h2>Who can edit</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Administrators</strong> — full create/edit by default</li>
  <li><strong>Agents</strong> — usually read-only unless custom role grants <code>knowledge_base_manage</code> (Enterprise)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Link from chat widget</h2>
<p>Point website widget or auto-replies to Help Center URLs so customers self-serve before chatting.</p>

<h2>Captain integration</h2>
<p>Connect Help Center articles as <a href="<%= guide_page_path('captain') %>#documents">Captain documents</a> so AI answers align with published content. Captain turns documents into searchable FAQs — see the <a href="<%= guide_page_path('captain') %>">Captain AI guide</a>.</p>

<h2>SEO & discovery</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Set meta title and description per article</li>
  <li>Use clear titles customers actually search for</li>
  <li>Submit sitemap to search engines if custom domain is configured</li>
</ul>

<h2>Help Center vs this User Guide</h2>
<table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:0.875rem; margin:1rem 0;">
  <thead>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align:left;">
      <th style="padding:0.5rem;">Resource</th>
